@node "Document_11" "What is the Filelister ??"
@toc "Document_10"
@next "Document_12"
@prev "Document_10"
 What is the Filelister ???

Who doesn`t know that problem ??? Your directory contains more than hundret
crunched files and you dosen`t remember the programm that I_Don`t_know.lha
contains. If you use Filelister that will have an end. Filelister creates
File- listings using the filename and the FileIdDiz in this form:

Lister.lha              ______________________________________
                       /\_____________________________________\
                      / /   __                                /
                     / /   /    / __  /   __ _/__ __         /
                    / /   /- / / /_/ / / /_  //_//_/        /
                   / /   /  / / /_  / / __/ //_ /  \       /
                   \/_____________________________________/
                    |  creates Filelistings with using   |
                    |   the Filename and the FileIdDiz   |
                    |____________________________________|

WithoutFileId.lha    no File Id availiable

Filelister can create a filelist for a whole directory, but you also can
create filelists with a specified startletter. With this option it is in fact
no problem to produce lists in alphabeticel orders ( in the moment only manual
-----> @{"see futur" link "Document_17" 0} ).
@endnode

@node "Document_12" "What do I need for the Filelister ??"
@toc "Document_10"
@next "Document_13"
@prev "Document_11"
 What do I need for the Filelister ??

At first you need an Amiga. I think the programm works on all 680XX Boards.
But it will be better for your nerves if you had a minimum Configuration of an
68020 an a minimum of 1 Mb Ram free. Because working on a 68000 can cost many
many time.

 How many Ram do I need ???

If you only scan for one File the needet Ram is small, if you scan hundret
files it is bigger. But I think, if you had 1 MB Ram ( is it not standart ??)
it is enough to work in little steps. If you have a "little" Amiga it will be
a good idea to scan for patterns and not a whole directory.

If the programm would not run on a standart Amiga 500 please mail it to me and
I will search for a solution of that problem ( address @{"see Author" link "Document_19" 0} ).

You also need a bit of sotfware from the Aminet that is not include in this
paggage :

            SnatchDiz Vers. 2.2 +      ( this is a Dizextractor )
    rexxreqtools.library Vers. 37.71   ( this is for the Requesters )

at least the cruncher-programms, but I think, everbody had them on his system
(if you are using a Modem).
@endnode

