@node "Document_14" "Installation"
@toc "Document_10"
@next "Document_15"
@prev "Document_13"
 Installation

If you want to install the Filelister you only had to doubleclick the
Installer.ENG (for English) or the Installer.GER (for German) icon. You do not
need the commodore installer, because the installscript is written in Arexx.

The Install script creates a directory called Filelister in the choosen path.
Then it`ll copy the following files to that directory :

             the arexx programm Filelister   + Filelister.info
             this guide file named Filelister.guide + info
             the default Icon for the filelists
             (if you want to change the default icon,
              just doubleclick the Icon and read the following ussage)

If the installscript is ready, you don`t have to reboot the computer, because
this script creates an assign wich is not for everytime. [ I`ve warned you, my
english is terrible :-) ] That means the assign is away if you reboot the
computer. If you want to use the Filelister always, you had to create an
assign in your s:user-startup like the following example (Filelister is
installt at the directory or partizion WORK: )

            ;Beginn Filelister
              assign Filelister: Work:Filelister/
            ;End Filelister


If you want to test the Filelister you can install the filelister into the Ram
Disk. if you switch of your computer ( or make a reboot) this installation
will be killed.
@endnode

@node "Document_15" "Using Filelister "
@toc "Document_10"
@next "Document_16"
@prev "Document_14"
How must I use the Filelister ???

I think the programm is written realy simple. I think a starting user can use
the programm like a intermediate or expert user. Just follow the Requesters.

At the first Requester the programm will ask you for the Destination Directory
where the filelists are saved.

At the second Requester it will ask you for the Directory where it had to
start working.

At the following requester you can secify a pattern (don`t delete the jokers
#? because the programm need them ).

At last theres a requester that will ask you for start scanning again oder end
the programm.

If you`ve scaned a whole directory and if you want to continue scanning
another directory, make sure that the old Filelist is renamed by hand, because
while scanning a whole directory theres made a filelist called Fileliste-all.
If you scan another Dir the programm comes in trouble, because the name of a
filelist exists. In this case it will break an nothing else will do from the
programm ( deleting help-files in the dir T: and so on ) this could be very
nervous if you`ve scanned for half an houer and the request is nothing. On
that problem im working on ( see futur ).
@endnode

